text: Bagdadia irakella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Hans Georg Amsel in 1949. It is found in Iraq.Bagdadia at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms ==References== Category:Bagdadia Category:Moths described in 1949 Category:Taxa named by Hans Georg Amsel
title: Bagdadia irakella
